title: Gegen die Wand - Head-on
description: Cahit is a German Turk at his late 30&#039;s. He has given up with his life after his beloved wife&#039;s death, and he&#039;s living a miserable life right in the core of cocaine and excessive drinking. One night, he semi-intentionally crashes into a wall, and barely survives. At the hospital he&#039;s taken to, he meets a girl, Sibel, another German Turk who&#039;s tried to commit suicide. She&#039;s sick and tired of her family&#039;s ultra-traditional issues, and asks Cahit to carry out a white marriage with her out of the blue, so that she can become a married woman and get rid of her family&#039;s revolting pressure. Cahit is turned off by the idea at first, but then he agrees to take part in this plan. As Sibel tells him straightaway that she&#039;s interested in absolute freedom involving other men and he agrees, they live as roommates with separate private lives for a while. Then things take a different turn, and they&#039;re no longer two indifferent roommates. But their love story won&#039;t be anywhere as simple as any other...
